The antenna configurations for this model appear to differ based on the unit shell color. The black model has RP-SMA connectors for all antennas. The white model has two integral antennas and one removable (RP-SMA).
This device uses 3x SiGe 5005L / Skyworks SE5005L (5GHz power amplifier).
This device is sold by '''LevelOne''' / '''DDC''' as the [[LevelOne WGR-8020]] (white model).
"11340Y20IU00003B1" and "2011/08/09" appears to be silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
Flash and RAM for this device may be the same as the [[OvisLink AirLive N450R]], 16MB and 64MB respectively.
Default credentials for this device are from the FCC manual. The FCC manual also states the default SSIDs are '''default_2.4g''' and '''default_5g'''.
00:50:18 ('''AMIT''') is a probable OUI for this device.
